The paper proposes a new approach to address the issue of posterior collapse in latent variable generative models. This is a problem that is commonly encountered in machine learning, particularly in the areas of natural language processing and computer vision. Given that the paper focuses on developing a new method for improving the performance of generative models, it is likely to be classified under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
